{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"01728f08-69c3-4882-8738-456cfd411d95","content":"Here are the **3 evaluation performance anti-patterns** in this project:\n\n---\n\n### 1. File I/O Property Function (line 13, `EvalHeavy.csproj`)\n```xml\n<BuildNotes>$([System.IO.File]::ReadAllText('build-notes.txt'))</BuildNotes>\n```\nProperty functions that perform file I/O execute during **evaluation** (before any targets run), blocking the evaluation pipeline. This runs on every build, even no-op builds.\n\n**Fix:** Move this into a target with `Inputs`/`Outputs` so it only runs when the file changes, or use `ReadLinesFromFile` task at execution time.\n\n---\n\n### 2. Overly Broad Glob (line 9, `EvalHeavy.csproj`)\n```xml\n<AdditionalFiles Include=\"**\\*.*\" Exclude=\"**\\bin\\**;**\\obj\\**\" />\n```\n`**\\*.*` walks the **entire directory tree** at evaluation time. This gets exponentially worse as the repo grows (e.g., `node_modules`, large asset folders). Only `bin`/`obj` are excluded.\n\n**Fix:** Scope the glob to specific extensions or directories, or add large directories to `DefaultItemExcludes`:\n```xml\n<DefaultItemExcludes>$(DefaultItemExcludes);node_modules\\**;.git\\**</DefaultItemExcludes>\n```\n\n---\n\n### 3. Deep Import Chain (3 levels)\n```\nEvalHeavy.csproj → level1.props → level2.props → level3.props\n```\nEach import adds an evaluation phase pass. At 3 levels this is modest, but it's a warning sign — chains beyond ~20 levels become a measurable bottleneck. Consider flattening if these grow.\n\n---\n\n**Priority:** Issue #1 (file I/O) and #2 (broad glob) are the most impactful. The import chain is low-risk at its current depth.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"1cd83c65-2db7-4524-93ef-38a3a99af612","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"Now I have a clear picture of the project. Let me analyze it for evaluation performance issues using my knowledge of MSBuild evaluation performance patterns.","outputTokens":516,"requestId":"5C17:3ED17A:5E31BDD:67448AC:69F15D16"},"id":"06641db5-11f3-4d39-881d-28b48719159f","timestamp":"2026-04-29T01:21:40.178Z","parentId":"2cb3cbf8-db21-49eb-9fe3-21de127d0efc"}
